0.title: The Story of FU
0.plot: Fired Up gets fueled up, fired up and just plain fired.

1.title: Fired Up and Throwing Down
1.plot: The Misfits prepare for their next project - a rare 2WD 1978 Blazer. But after one of their long-time partners decides to quit, have they hit a roadblock?

2.title: Blaze It Up
2.plot: After Richard Rawlings blocks Fired Up Garage from entering the Lone Star Throwdown truck show, they must race to finish their build in order to find a buyer. But will a mountain of mismatched aftermarket parts bring this garage to its knees?

3.title: X Marks the Parts
3.plot: Thomas finds a rare but pristine '68 AMC AMX. But, finding parts for this American Motor Experimental car makes this one of the toughest builds yet!

4.title: Wires and Misfires
4.plot: With trying to put the 1968 AMC AMX engine and transmission together, the mechanics find themselves in a circus of misfit parts and process. Will the guys be able to find their way through wires and misfires?

5.title: Street Fighting 70 1/2 Camaro
5.plot: Thomas finds a 70 1/2 Camaro on the side of the road. After a tough negotiation with the owner, the Fired Up Garage team takes the Camaro home.

6.title: A Jurassic Sized Adventure
6.plot: Chris Pratt has reached out to Fired Up Garage, personally, to request a custom bike inspired by the blockbuster Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom.

7.title: United Kingdom of Misfits
7.plot: Thomas gets his hands dirty when he finds a '61 Morris Minor hidden in a pile of dirt. The team put some American swagger into the vintage British car.

8.title: Minor Fire
8.plot: With a deadline looming, the boys aim to finish building their first ever foreign import - a 1961 Morris Minor. And, Thomas unearths a 1932 Ford Model A Roadster.

9.title: Orange You Glad
9.plot: Fired Up Garage get their hands on a 1964 GMC Truck, a popular work vehicle. But problems arise right after John Klump and the team start work on the tough truck.

10.title: Pound Town
10.plot: The guys work on completing the 1964 GMC Truck. John Klump and his team deal with parts issues and Richard stops by for money from the "Tom Weight Loss" wager.

11.title: Barter Bucket
11.plot: The Misfits take on a 1927 Ford Model T coup, to turn it into a version of the classic hot rod known as the "T Bucket". Plus, who will win the Tom vs. Richard race?

12.title: The Cooler
12.plot: After the "bucket" for the Misfits' classic T Bucket hot rod build comes back from paint in a vibrant shade of yellow, the guys mount the body onto the chassis and John decides to tackle the wiring. Will the Misfits win their race with Richard Rawlings?

1.title: Fired Up About a '67 Chevelle, Part 1
1.plot: "Fired Up Garage" goes to work on a '67 Chevelle. The team also enters a demolition derby for publicity, running into former co-workers of the shop they were all fired from by Richard Rawlings and who they later find out is their new shop landlord.

2.title: Fired Up About a '67 Chevelle, Part 2
2.plot: "Fired Up Garage" struggles to deal with "landlord" Richard Rawlings, as well as the completion of their first major build. Will theamazing '67 Chevelle redo put "Fired Up Garage" on the map, ready to go toe-to-toe with Richard and "Gas Monkey Garage."

3.title: Jazzed About a '57 Gasser, Part 1
3.plot: Thomas makes a profit flipping a car Richard turned his nose up at. Meanwhile, Thomas and Scot pick up solid a '57 Chevy for their next build. Later, the shop is threatened when a tree falls on it, ruining their office and crushing a customer's truck.

4.title: Jazzed About a '57 Gasser, Part 2
4.plot: Richard surprises FU garage with a rundown trailer as a replacement office. Scot has a buyer for the '57 gasser and gives the crew a two-week deadline, but things come to a halt after Thomas builds an engine that's unacceptable with the other partners.

5.title: Furious '65 Fastback, Part 1
5.plot: The Misfits open house is shut down by Richard Rawlings.Thomas picks up a rare Ford Torino Cobra. Up a creek without a project car, the team hastily buys a '65 Mustang fastback . Meanwhile, Thomas finds a '69 Barracuda that he allows Tom to fix.

6.title: Furious '65 Fastback, Part 2
6.plot: The mustang comes back from paint and the guys get to work. A trip to Gas Monkey to use a tool costs them extra money when Richard catches them and invoices them. Things take a bigger turn for the worst when Soupbone gets white paint on the hood.

7.title: One Nasty '65 Nova, Part 1
7.plot: Thomas flips classic 2 cars that turn a quick profit: a '53 Mercury and a '58 Ford Fairlane. Thomas and Scot pick up a'65 Chevy Nova that Scot's dad did all the engine work on, but Corbett goes rogue and paints the car charcoal grey instead of white.

8.title: One Nasty '65 Nova, Part 2
8.plot: In this part II, Scot recovers from Corbett's big paint surprise; the team hustle to finish their Nova while Thomas goes on the hunt for a classic hot rod; after a long haul, the entire Misfits team celebrates at Rednecks with Paychecks.

1.title: Flipped for a '69 Chevy Shortbed, Part 1
1.plot: Thomas and Scot roll into FU with their first truck project, but disaster strikes when Scot and Austin pick up the newly painted '69 Chevy cab and bed. Thomas must decide whether he wants to build up a '59 Oldsmobile, or keep as an original relic.

2.title: Flipped for a '69 Chevy Shortbed, Part 2
2.plot: FU Garage must deal with the aftermath of the demolished '69 Chevy Pickup . Jordan and Tom look for a replacement cab, while Thomas tries to flip a '59 Oldsmobile to deal with the unforeseen costs.

3.title: A Rusty, Crusty '67 Camaro, Part 1
3.plot: Thomas brings home a rusted '67 Camaro that the entire team is excited to get to work on, except for Scot and Austin. As the garage keeps busy repairing the Camaro, Scot refuses to work on something he believes won't make any money.

4.title: A Rusty, Crusty '67 Camaro, Part 2
4.plot: In the wake of Scot and Austin quitting the garage, the Fired Up guys call on friends and family to help prep and repair the '67 Camaro. Meanwhile, Thomas and Tom have their eye on '73 Firebird.

5.title: A '31 Ford Hot Rod and '71 Holy Grail Cuda
5.plot: The '31 Ford build has been at a stand still until the necessary parts finally arrive and the build can move forward, but a wiring mistake from Kevin almost burns the car to ground . Thomas purchases another '71 Cuda, but this time from Richard.

6.title: The '71 Holy Grail Cuda/Goodbye Little Richard
6.plot: While the guys work on tearing down the '71 Cuda, Scot and Austin arrive to see if they Fired Up guys need any assistance, since they've got two big projects on their hands. Thomas and Tom flip a '51 Chevy truck. Tom also says goodbye to Little Richard.

7.title: The Race to the Finish the 71 Holy Grail Cuda
7.plot: The guys continue building the '71 Cuda but run into several fitting issues. The Fired Up Garage future also hangs by a thread, when they can't get the '71 Cuda engine running - potentially denying them their largest payday.

8.title: Revving Up the 31 Ford Hotrod
8.plot: The '31 Ford build has been at a stand still until the necessary parts finally arrive and the build can move forward, but a wiring mistake from Kevin almost burns the car to ground . Thomas purchases another '71 Cuda, but this time from Richard.

1.title: Launching a '69 Satellite
1.plot: The "Fired Up Garage" guys buy their next build: a '69 Plymouth Satellite to turn it into a racer with a 750-hp big block 440 engine. Thomas Weeks has his eyes on a '32 Ford Five-Window Body owned by Richard Rawlings.

2.title: Launching a '69 Satellite, Part 2
2.plot: The "Fired Up team attempts to finish the 1969 Plymouth Satellite after flaring tempers lead to a blow-up between Tom & Thomas. Thomas and Kevin are having a bad day pickin' and are about to call it quits, until they come across a 1954 Ford F100.

3.title: Crushed GTO and Chopped '41 Ford
3.plot: Tom & Thomas buy a '71 Pontiac GTO and it quickly becomes apparent that much of the body is rusted. Thomas visits Gas Monkey Garage looking to make a purchase from Richard. The Fired up team buys a '41 Ford from a friend and make it their next big build.

4.title: Crushed GTO and Chopped '41 Ford, Part 2
4.plot: The "Fired Up Garage" team teaches Thomas a lesson by taking the 1971 GTO to a field and crushing it with a tank. Thomas buys a 1941 Ford to turn it into a flaming blue hot rod as well as a food truck to kick start the dream of a Fired Up Garage empire!

5.title: '57 Corvette, Part 1
5.plot: Thomas Weeks & Tom Smith get a'57 Corvette for a bargain & help Sue Yu-Lan Martin purchase a '56 Ford Truck that the "Fired Up Garage" will rebuild. Tom's food truck arrives & Soup Bone drops the ball on parts as a new team member is brought on.

6.title: 57 Corvette, Part 2
6.plot: Soup Bone fails to get parts in time and pays the price. After weeks of delays the Misfits finish the '57 Corvette and look for a big payday. Richard Rawlings casts doubts on whether the guys can make it a go with their Food Truck.

7.title: Sue's Custom 56 Ford
7.plot: Having sold the '57 Corvette for $80,000 the guys start on Sue Yu-Lan Martin's '56 Ford truck. The truck takes over 3 weeks to paint & Tom Smith has overspent,so he flips a '55 Dodge Royal Lancer, flips the '64 Thunderbird, & even asks Sue for an advance.

8.title: Sue's Custom 56 Ford, Part 2
8.plot: Thomas and Tom pick up a rusted but original '67 Chevelle to flip for money towards Sue Yu-Lan's Martin's '56 Ford truck. Sue gets angry with the length of the build and brings Richard Rawlings into the fold.

1.title: Guardian of the Galaxie
1.plot: Fired Up Garage faces a dilemma while trying to complete Sue's truck; the shop begins work on a Ford Galaxie; plans of garage expansion cause tension.

2.title: Galaxie Quest: Barrett Jackson
2.plot: With Jordan out of the picture and a looming Barrett-Jackson deadline, John Klump steps in to help the team. As the time comes for the Ford Galaxie to face the auction block, the Misfits begin to realize what's at stake.

3.title: Wrestling with Disaster
3.plot: Fired Up brings in a rusty, decrepit 1961 Ford Econoline pickup, but when Tom discovers a hidden treasure, he goes searching for legendary Mexican Luchador, Blue Demon Jr. and uncovers more than he bargained for.

4.title: Truckin' It with Trejo
4.plot: Fired Up attempts to sell the Econoline to the notorious, Danny Trejo. Can Thomas seal the deal and make it a Hollywood ending or will the Econoline bomb blow up in their faces. Also, Tom takes on a legendary Latino wrestler.

5.title: The Original Rum Runner
5.plot: Thom and Tom race out to Georgia to take a hot lap with Legendary NASCAR driver Bill Elliot and bring home a 40 Ford Tudor sedan to transform into a vintage Moonshine Unner. But when pressures mount from this high-end hot rod build, tensions boil over.

6.title: Booze in the Hood
6.plot: Josh, Klump and Kevin continue to work on the restoration of the vintage 40 Ford Moonshine Runner. However, Klump gets hot under the collar and threatens to leave the entire build. Thomas buys a 60 Cadillac from his high school sweetheart.

7.title: Klump in the Road
7.plot: Thomas and Tom acquire a rare first, generation 1959 Chevy El Camino, but excitement turns to despair when the cars deteriorated condition gives John Klump second thoughts about the build and forces him to make a decision about his involvement with FUG.

8.title: What Klump?
8.plot: Thomas surprises Klump with an offer to become a partner at FUG. Thomas then goes on a spending spree adding two extra cars to the garage's inventory. Meanwhile, problems arise on the El Camino build. It'll be a race to the finish for the Misfits.

1.title: Spurred for a Ford
1.plot: Thomas tracks down a rare original 1932 Ford Tudor! As the shop makes plans to build this into their finest car yet, Thomas doubles down with hopes of expanding the business by sponsoring a red-hot bull rider and committing to sell the '32 Ford.

2.title: Boom or Bust
2.plot: The Misfits continue to work on the restoration of their vintage '32 Ford. Thomas throws a wrench in the plans and decides to take the car and the Misfits to the Barrett-Jackson all expenses paid.

3.title: Air Picking We Shall Go
3.plot: Thomas and Tom take car hunting to a whole new level by using a plane to "Air Pick" and search for an elusive Honey hole. Instead, they find and buy a 55' Chevy Bel Air to build.

4.title: Chasing a Six Figure Dream
4.plot: The guys push to finish every hot rodder's dream car - a Tri Five Chevy Belair, a car so hot that even NASCAR driver Elliot Sadler wants a sneak peek.

5.title: Fired Up for a Jeep
5.plot: The guy's circumvent Thomas and buy back a 1952 Willys Jeep previously flipped with the intention of building the ultimate off-road machine! With no buyer, the misfits pull out all the stops and decide to showcase the Jeep at "Rednecks With Paychecks."

6.title: Muddy Payday
6.plot: John Klump returns to the Fired Up Garage with the Jeep Willy's painted the wrong color. Thomas and Tom make a deal on a vintage sixty-four GTI then attempt to trick Klump into thinking they are building the vehicle.

7.title: Gleams with a Sunliner
7.plot: Tom Smith and Jordan Butler were fired by Richard Rawlings from 'Fast N' Loud'. Now they have teamed up with Thomas Weeks to start their own garage as equal partners.

8.title: Stars Align
8.plot: Tom Smith and Jordan Butler were fired by Richard Rawlings from 'Fast N' Loud'. Now they have teamed up with Thomas Weeks to start their own garage as equal partners.

9.title: Fair Game for a Fairlane
9.plot: Fired up takes on a '67 Ford Fairlane GTA to turn into a Pro street machine. Thomas works on a '73 AMC Gremlin for a doughnut-themed World Record attempt.

10.title: Fairlane Gets Fired Up
10.plot: Tom shoots for world record glory while the rest of the shop pushes ahead on the Fairlane build, but when Richard makes a play to buy the garage from Phipps, Fired Up's future is put in jeopardy!

-1.title: Misfit Mischief
-1.plot: The mechanics from Fired Up Garage are ready to rumble, when they get wind Richard Rawlings and the Street Racers from the 405 are holding a rematch. The Misfits challenge Farmtruck and AZN to an all out 30 lap, three-driver road course race.

locations: Dallas, Texas, USA::(Old Gas Monkey Garage building)
imdb.plot outline: As things went in the workshop at Gas Monkey there was conflict and disagreements... Some which got certain guys either fired or forced them to take the road. But no, they aint giving up just yet. The fired up their own garage in the hopes of becoming a worthy rival for Gas Monkey.

But no, they aint giving up just yet. The fired up their own garage in the hopes of becoming a worthy rival for Gas Monkey.::Ryko Breytenbach
